We’re on a mission to increase the healthspan for all, and our patented PhenOM Foundation Model is moving us closer every day. It’s enabling powerful insights into rare diseases and helping patients with complex, hard-to-diagnose conditions receive the right treatment at the right time.

Exciting to be part of a team turning possibility into impact.

We are hiring. Join OM1 and use your data skills to improve patient outcomes. We're a leader in Real-World Evidence (RWE) and AI, turning complex healthcare data into critical insights.

We're currently seeking India-based Clinical Data/Analytics Engineers to accelerate OM1's Real World Data Cloud. You'll analyze, transform, standardize, and enrich clinical data from a variety of EMRs and claims data sources, making it ready for impactful RWE use cases.

Key Skills:
-Strong SQL skills in data transformation and analysis, particularly in modern clouds such as Snowflake.
-Experience with scripting languages (python/R) or working with notebooks like Jupyter/Databricks/Hex.
-Experience with Healthcare Data, particularly EHR and Claims data and clinical terminologies (ICD, SNOMED, etc.).
-Experience: 3-5 years in healthcare data processing (ETL + Analysis).
-Experience building datasets or product features that are delivered directly to customers.

Why OM1? Your work directly contributes to accelerating clinical research and improving lives.

Apply now by emailing your resume to

I'll be at 
hashtag
#AAD2025 this Thursday (March 6th) thru Sunday (March 9th). Would love to meet up if you will be there.

Critical mental health outcomes are often hidden in unstructured clinical notes rather than in structured real-world data.

Since 2015, OM1 has led the way in AI-driven real-world data insights for mental health, extracting relevant clinical elements from unstructured data. OM1’s patented technology estimates PHQ-9 scores, finds suicidal ideation, and defines anhedonia from psychiatrist notes – providing deeper, more accurate patient insights that are critical in the fight against rising mental illness.

Take a look at our patented technology in action ⬇️

✅ Natural Language Processing to Extract Depression Symptom Severity and Suicide Ideation from Clinical Notes:
✅ Medical Language Processing in RWD to Understand Antidepressant Side Effects:
✅ Weight gain and comorbidities associated with oral second-generation antipsychotics:
Very excited to be joining this great group to discuss how we can be pragmatic about pragmatic trials
